The paper discusses the SemEval-2015 Task 3 on Answer Selection in Community Question Answering, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques to classify answers as good, bad, or potentially relevant with respect to a given question. This falls under the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
